## Limitations

This report is limited by the availability of up-to-date data and the complexity of human trafficking, which varies significantly across different regions and cultures. Additionally, the effectiveness of proposed solutions can be difficult to measure due to the clandestine nature of trafficking activities. Further research and continuous monitoring are necessary to adapt strategies to evolving trafficking methods and trends.